Description:
Tatiana was killed in her apartment.

> OAKLAND - A 23-year-old [trans woman] was found dead in [her] apartment Saturday, killed by mysterious means, authorities said.
>
> Police identified the man as [deadname] Rivers, who was also known as Tatiana Rivers, or Keymani Howard. Deputy Coroner Kevin Hinkle said the death was "definitely" a homicide, but said there was no indication of how the [woman] was killed.
>
> "There's no blunt trauma, no stab wounds, nothing to explain what happened," he said. He added, however, that there was evidence of a struggle in the apart ment, which is in a quiet wooded area near Mills College.
>
> No weapons were found, he said, and there were no visible wounds on the body.
>
> Asked how it was clear the death was a homicide, Hinkle said, "The way the body was found - just the position and what have you." He would not elaborate. "This is a case that needs an autopsy to determine what the cause of death is," agreed Deputy Coroner Frank Gentle. "It didn't look natural."
>
> Oakland police were called to the apartment, in the 6100 block of Seminary Avenue, at 1:09 p.m. Saturday. Homicide investigators confirmed that they had interviewed people in the case at the police station, but would not call anyone a suspect. They said no arrests had been made.
